column1: title
BTAA GDP Accession Guidelines for ArcGIS Open Data Portals (../metadata/arcgis-harvest-policy-2018/)
column4: Deprecated. This document describes the BTAA GDP Accession Guidelines for ArcGIS Open Data Portals, including eligible sites and records, harvest schedules, and remediation work. This policy may change at any time in response to updates to the ArcGIS Open Data Portal platform and/or the BTAA GDP harvesting and remediation processes.

column1: Best Practices for ArcGIS Hub/Open Data Portals
column4: This guide presents publishing workflows that improve the stability of data identifiers and maximize benefits from metadata of resources on ArcGIS Hub / Open Data Portals.

column1: Maintaining Access To Ephemeral Resources vs Archived Data
column4: This document compares the BTAA GDP staff time required for maintaining access to ephemeral resources vs archiving them in a spatial repository. It does not estimate costs for building a spatial repository or additional staff or training that it might require. a university-managed spatial repository and providing stable linkages.
